<T>__{dissolve to:}
<L>__{interior upper east side apartment. day.}
<A>__{a newborn baby boy, nicolai, plays in the wrapping paper of opened gifts beneath an extravagantly decorated christmas tree.}
<D>__{new york december 25, 1991}
<C>__{yuri }
<D>__{i was still living way beyond my means, mortgaged to the hilt, using one credit card to payoff another. anything to keep ava in the style to which she had, thanks largely to me, become accustomed. then suddenly all my christmases came at once.}
<A>__{a family christmas anatoly, irina and ava open gifts. baby nicolai wriggles on a blanket, trying to reach a piece of tinsel.}
<C>__{anatoly}
<P>__{(to irina, regarding a nativity scene on a christmas card)}
<D>__{jesus was jewish. you're worshipping a jew.}
<A>__{irina ignores him. she regards a gift a silver goblet set from tiffany's.}
<C>__{irina}
<D>__{ava, this is too much.}
<C>__{ava}
<D>__{yuri likes to spoil you.}
<A>__{nicolai crawls an inch. ava beams proudly.}
<C>__{ava}
<D>__{nicki! you did it. good boy!}
<C>__{anatoly}
<D>__{that's my grandson.}
<A>__{ava looks around for yuri.}
<C>__{ava}
<P>__{(calling out)}
<D>__{yuri. don't you want to see what your son is doing?}
<A>__{no reply. ava wraps the piece of tinsel around the baby's head. a loud shout from the other room.}
<C>__{yuri }
<D>__{tak! tak! tak fucking tak! (subtitle:}
<P>__{yes!)}
<A>__{ava scoops up the baby. with anatoly and irina, they go to investigate. on the television, mikhail gorbachev, is making his famous speech, officially ending the cold war. yuri kneels in front of the tv as if it is an altar.}
<C>__{anatoly}
<D>__{what the hell's the matter?}
